<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1997-01-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Murine coronavirus infection: a paradigm for virus-induced demyelinating disease</TITLE><BODY>A variety of neurological diseases in humans, including multiple sclerosis (MS), have been postulated to have a viral etiology. The use of animal models provides insights into potential mechanism(s) involved in the disease process. The murine coronavirus-induced demyelinating disease in rodents is one such model for demyelinating disease in humans.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>